  • Constructor Details

    • Car

      public Car(double posX, double posY, Direction dir)
      Sets the appearance, position and direction of the car. Cars have an acceleration of 2.32m/s^2 and a random max. speed within the maxspeed range set by the simulation, at least 10km/h (i.e. 1.111px per tick).
      Parameters:
      posX - The X position of the car on the scene
      posY - The Y position of the car on the scene
      dir - The direction the car should start moving in

  • Method Details

    • moveVehicle

      public void moveVehicle()
      Translates the car according to the current direction. Cars with Behaviour.RECKLESS will try to overtake every car in front of them, those with cautious behavior will adjust their speed to slower vehicles in front of them. Cars with Behaviour.SEMI will drive cautiously or recklessly with a chance of 50%.
      Specified by:
      moveVehicle in class Vehicle
      See Also:
      • Vehicle.move(Direction)
